      "metaDescription": "WHO warns that antimicrobial resistance is becoming a major global health crisis in 2026.",
      "article": "The World Health Organization has issued an urgent warning regarding the rapid rise of antimicrobial resistance worldwide. According to recent estimates, antibiotic-resistant infections now cause more than 1.27 million deaths every year globally. Health experts stated that excessive antibiotic use, self-medication, and misuse in agriculture are accelerating resistance among harmful bacteria. The WHO warned that common infections may become untreatable if countries fail to regulate antibiotic consumption and improve healthcare systems. Governments have been advised to increase investment in research, public awareness campaigns, and hospital infection control measures. Medical researchers are also encouraging pharmaceutical companies to develop new antibiotics and alternative treatments. Public health specialists emphasized that immediate international cooperation is necessary to prevent a future health emergency. The warning has raised serious concerns among healthcare professionals about the growing threat of drug-resistant diseases across both developed and developing countries."
