      "article": "India’s newly announced Artificial Intelligence policy has triggered widespread discussions regarding its long-term impact on citizens, businesses, and digital governance. The government stated that the policy aims to promote innovation, improve public services, and strengthen India’s position in the global technology sector. The policy encourages AI adoption in healthcare, education, agriculture, cybersecurity, and governance systems. However, critics argue that large technology corporations may benefit more than ordinary citizens due to their financial and technological advantages. Concerns have also been raised regarding data privacy, surveillance, algorithmic bias, and employment disruption caused by automation. Technology experts emphasized the need for stronger regulations, transparent AI systems, and public accountability mechanisms. Supporters of the policy believe it can boost economic growth, digital infrastructure, and startup development. The debate highlights the challenge of balancing technological advancement with ethical responsibility and citizen rights in the digital age."
